Use the standard library
This is how to minPath of grid and k:
  Remember that rows is grid's length
  Remember that cols is item 0 in grid's length
  Remember that dp is []
  Remember that path is []

  Do this rows times:
    Add dp to []
    Add path to []
  End do

  Remember that r is 0
  Do this rows times:
    Remember that rowVals is []
    Remember that rowPath is []
    Remember that c is 0
    Do this cols times:
      Add rowVals to 0
      Add rowPath to []
      Increase c
    End do
    Remember that item r in dp is rowVals
    Remember that item r in path is rowPath
    Increase r
  End do

  Remember that item 0 in item 0 in dp is item 0 in item 0 in grid
  Remember that item 0 in item 0 in path is [1]

  Remember that c is 1
  Do this diff of cols and 1 times:
    Remember that item c in item 0 in dp is sum of item diff of c and 1 in item 0 in dp and item c in item 0 in grid
    Remember that prevPath is item diff of c and 1 in item 0 in path
    Remember that newPath is []
    Remember that i is 0
    Do this prevPath's length times:
      Add newPath to item i in prevPath
      Increase i
    End do
    Add newPath to 2
    Remember that item c in item 0 in path is newPath
    Increase c
  End do

  Remember that r is 1
  Do this diff of rows and 1 times:
    Remember that item 0 in item r in dp is sum of item 0 in item diff of r and 1 in dp and item 0 in item r in grid
    Remember that prevPath is item 0 in item diff of r and 1 in path
    Remember that newPath is []
    Remember that i is 0
    Do this prevPath's length times:
      Add newPath to item i in prevPath
      Increase i
    End do
    Add newPath to 1
    Remember that item 0 in item r in path is newPath

    Remember that c is 1
    Do this diff of cols and 1 times:
      Remember that fromTop is sum of item c in item diff of r and 1 in dp and item c in item r in grid
      Remember that fromLeft is sum of item diff of c and 1 in item r in dp and item c in item r in grid

      When fromTop is less than fromLeft, then:
        Remember that item c in item r in dp is fromTop
        Remember that prevPath is item c in item diff of r and 1 in path
        Remember that newPath is []
        Remember that i is 0
        Do this prevPath's length times:
          Add newPath to item i in prevPath
          Increase i
        End do
        Add newPath to 1
        Remember that item c in item r in path is newPath
      But, if not:
        Remember that item c in item r in dp is fromLeft
        Remember that prevPath is item diff of c and 1 in item r in path
        Remember that newPath is []
        Remember that i is 0
        Do this prevPath's length times:
          Add newPath to item i in prevPath
          Increase i
        End do
        Add newPath to 2
        Remember that item c in item r in path is newPath
      End when

      Increase c
    End do

    Increase r
  End do

  Remember that fullPath is item diff of cols and 1 in item diff of rows and 1 in path
  Remember that answer is []
  Remember that i is 0
  Do this min of k and fullPath's length times:
    Add answer to item i in fullPath
    Increase i
  End do

  The answer is answer
Now you know